    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Spend less time cooking and make dinner work around you.</strong></p><p>Before you begin, get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>You can only heat your food once, then enjoy straight away</p><p>Note: Microwave ovens vary. Make sure you heat food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-breast-red-pepper-and-rice-with-garlic-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-breast-red-pepper-and-rice-with-garlic-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add most of your <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save a little for later!) to a large heatproof bowl with a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> and your <strong>peri peri spice mix </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Put the bowl in the<strong> microwave</strong> for an initial 30 secs, then stir and return to the microwave for 20 secs or until the butter is completely melted \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-breast-red-pepper-and-rice-with-garlic-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and give it a good mix up and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-breast-red-pepper-and-rice-with-garlic-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of<strong> cooked long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-breast-red-pepper-and-rice-with-garlic-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>mayo</strong> and the <strong>remaining garlic </strong>to a small bowl with a splash of <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> garlic mayo</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-breast-red-pepper-and-rice-with-garlic-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is piping hot, add the <strong>cooked rice</strong> to the bowl with the peri peri sauce</p><p>Shred your <strong>cooked chicken </strong>and add to the bowl with your <strong>roasted red peppers </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until well combined, then put the bowl in the microwave for 30 secs - 1 min or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri chicken breast, red pepper & rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-breast-red-pepper-and-rice-with-garlic-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>peri peri chicken breast, red pepper & rice</strong> in bowls and top with the <strong>garlic mayo </strong>and <strong>salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle over a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
